  "judge_reasoning": "This is a well-established geographical fact. Mount Everest is definitively located within the Himalayas mountain range and sits on the border between Nepal and the Tibet Autonomous Region of China. The claim survived both advocacy and attack - Proposer verified all 3 atoms successfully, Challenger failed to falsify. Role-switch test showed divergence of 0.237 with no sycophancy detected. The claim is straightforward and verifiable. Minor uncertainties exist around exact elevation measurements (8,848m vs 8,848.86m) and precise border demarcation, but these do not affect the core geographical assertion. The volatility score is 0.0 because geographical features do not relocate on human timescales.",
  "what_would_change_verdict": "Evidence showing Mount Everest is NOT in the Himalayas or NOT on the Nepal-China border would flip this verdict. For example, if authoritative cartographic sources (UN, national surveys) relocated it elsewhere, or if geological evidence showed it belongs to a different range, this would be falsified. The current claim aligns with all major geographical authorities.",
